&lt;p&gt;Sandwell and West Birmingham Hospitals NHS Trust&#39;s School Nursing service is an innovative and driven service delivering public health services to the school aged population across Sandwell. The opportunity has arisen to join the service as a Specialist Community Public Health nursing student (School Nursing ). You will be a motivated individual who is passionate about supporting children, young people and their families. You will have a keen interest in public health agenda and the vast needs of the 5 - 19 population. We welcome applications from qualified nurses or midwives who meet the person specification, have current NMC registration, a full driving licence and access to a vehicle.You will be required to provide a portfolio of development and evidence of continued professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHeidi Ferrier - HixonJob titleTeam LeaderEmail addressSWBH.SHNSandwell@nhs.netTelephone number0121 6122974&lt;/p&gt;
